<font color="#FF0000">THOUGHTS, POSITIVE THINGS</font><br>
<tt>Sun Oct 19 20:44:04 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
The positive side of my Vietnam experience....that is a very *good* question.<br><br>
As I see it for myself, the positive aspects lie somewhere along a line between pairs of opposites. I have been told that I am one of the fortunate ones, having converted the darker side of things into a profession, a drive to prevent harm and death. I feel confident that I have succeeded, but at a price. <br><br>
Right now, I am working to moderate that pair of opposites so I can continue doing what I love and do best, but in a &quot;better&quot; way. It is interesting, but the &quot;drive&quot; I confused with true pride in my work. As I now look backward, I see my accomplishments in a different, more rewarding light.<br><br>
I feel the positive accomplishments of Vietnam Veterans is enhanced with a broader view of human nature, for better or for worse, and an appreciation for the value of life. These attributes are truly positive, and cannot help but influence whatever many of us do.<br><br>
I will work on these thoughts some more. <br><br>
